{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"This theme overrides the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Orange theme","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" for some colors so as to bring an “inverse”-colored experience.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is an override of the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesorange\/"},{"type":"text","text":" with some inverted colors. It can override any properties from its superclass. We did not plan to make "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" derivable."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The aim of the theme is to provide a particular set of colors for dedicated applications and use cases, like for example B2B apps or teams needing eye comfort. It can be seen as an extended dark mode."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"How-to-use-the-theme","level":2,"text":"How to use the theme"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme","isActive":true},{"text":" directly. You will have to use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"text":" for your root view and give it an instance of ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme","isActive":true},{"text":". Keep in mind the themes are ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift class objects"}]},{"text":" and can be heavy, so you may use only as instance as singleton and not store any properties.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import OUDS \/\/ To get OUDSThemeableView","import OUDSThemeInverse \/\/ To get Inverseheme","import SwiftUI","","@main","struct YourApp: App {","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            OUDSThemeableView(theme: InverseTheme()) {","                \/\/ Your root view","            }","        }","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then, in your views, you can simply use the theme through an environment variable to get the tokens:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import OUDS \/\/ To get the theme environment variable","import SwiftUI","","struct SomeView: View {","","    \/\/ Get OUDS environment variable for theme thanks to themeable view","    @Environment(\\.theme) var theme","    ","    var body: some View {","        ","        \/\/ Use the theme to retrieve the tokens","        \/\/ For spaces: theme.spaces","        \/\/ For sizes: theme.sizes","        \/\/ For borders: theme.borders","        \/\/ For elevations: theme.elevations","        \/\/ For opacities: theme.opacities","        \/\/ For colors: theme.colors","    }","}",""]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Framework","symbolKind":"module","modules":[{"name":"OUDSThemesInverse"}],"title":"OUDSThemesInverse","role":"collection","externalID":"OUDSThemesInverse"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudsthemesinverse"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Group","anchor":"Group","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"references":{"doc://ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse/documentation/OUDSThemesInverse":{"url":"\/documentation\/oudsthemesinverse","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"This theme overrides the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Orange theme"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" for some colors so as to bring an “inverse”-colored experience.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse","kind":"symbol","title":"OUDSThemesInverse","role":"collection"},"doc://ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse/documentation/OUDSThemesInverse/InverseTheme":{"url":"\/documentation\/oudsthemesinverse\/inversetheme","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"InverseTheme","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This is an override of the default basic "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OrangeTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" with some inverted colors."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It can overrides any properties from its superclass, but is not derivable."}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme","title":"InverseTheme","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"InverseTheme","kind":"identifier"}]},"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudsthemesorange/":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Orange theme"}],"url":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesorange\/","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesorange\/","title":"Orange theme"}}}